article.headline: Stanford 87, Oregon St. 82
article.story: STANFORD, Calif. -- Chasson Randle matched his season high with 24 points, Aaron Bright added 20 and Stanford beat Oregon State 87-82 on Thursday night. Anthony Brown had 11 points, and Josh Owens added nine points and recorded his 500th career rebound for the Cardinal (18-8, 8-6 Pac-12). Jared Cunningham scored 22 points and Roberto Nelson 19 for the Beavers (15-11, 5-9 Pac-12), who lost their third straight. Devon Collier had 13 points and Angus Brandt 11. Oregon State outscored the Cardinal 17-8 over the final 7:36 of the first half to take a 41-40 lead into intermission.
